# Module Architecture Rules

Follow:

- `docs/01-architecture.md` (canonical)
- `docs/08-module-architecture.md`

---

# Module Location

## Backend
- `backend/Template.Core/Features/{FeatureName}/`
- `backend/Template.Infrastructure/Features/{FeatureName}/`
- `backend/Template.API/CoreFeatures/{FeatureName}/`

## Frontend
- `frontend/src/features/{feature-name}/`

---

# Business Module Flow

Backend:

```text
Controller
↓
Handler / Use Case
↓
Repository Interface
↓
Repository Implementation
↓
Database
```

Frontend:

```text
Page / Component
↓
Hook
↓
API Client
↓
Backend API
```

---

# Backend Module Structure

```text
Template.Core/Features/{FeatureName}/
├── Commands/
├── Queries/
├── Handlers/
└── Interfaces/

Template.Infrastructure/Features/{FeatureName}/
└── Repositories/

Template.API/CoreFeatures/{FeatureName}/
└── {FeatureName}Controller.cs
```

Business logic lives in `Template.Core`.
Persistence lives in `Template.Infrastructure`.
HTTP entry points live in `Template.API`.

---

# Frontend Module Structure

```text
frontend/src/features/{feature-name}/
├── components/
├── pages/
├── hooks/
├── api/
├── schemas/
├── types/
└── index.ts
```

Pages render UI.
Hooks manage state and data fetching.
API clients call backend endpoints.
Schemas use Zod.

---

# Repository Rule

Database access only inside repositories.

Never access database directly from:

- pages
- components
- hooks
- controllers

Repositories should prefer `AsNoTracking()` for read-only queries.

---

# Use Case Rule

Business logic belongs in backend use cases / handlers.

Do not place business logic in:

- pages
- components
- hooks
- repositories
- controllers

---

# Auth Module Exception

`auth` is a platform module, not a business module.

Backend:
- `backend/Template.API/CoreFeatures/Auth/`
- `backend/Template.Core/Features/Auth/`
- `backend/Template.Infrastructure/Auth/`

Frontend:
- `frontend/src/features/auth/`

Auth provider implementations belong in `backend/Template.Infrastructure/Auth/`.
Auth orchestration belongs in the auth feature slice.

---

# Shared Code

Shared reusable code belongs in:

- `frontend/src/shared/`
- `Template.Core/Common/`

Use shared code only when logic or UI is reused by multiple features.

---

# Module Isolation

Features should be loosely coupled.
Avoid direct access to another feature's internal files.

---

# Tenant Model

Current architecture:

One Customer = One Database

Do not add `organization_id` to new tables unless explicitly requested.

---

# Goal

Modules must be:

- independent
- reusable
- scalable
- maintainable
- AI friendly
- predictable across backend and frontend

